text: Spins per second RPM ¼ 15 ½ 30 1 60 2 120 5 300 10 600 25 1500 Revolutions per minute, sometimes called RPM, is a measure of angular frequency. It means the number of times something spins in one minute. For example, if a wheel spins one time in one second, it is doing 60 RPM, because there is 60 seconds in one minute. Category:Units of frequency
title: Revolutions per minute
